1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,639
I want you to see that I'm serious
and sincere.

2
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:11,680
That's why I said it in front of my mom,

3
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,080
to make things clear.

4
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:18,520
<i>I don't believe they love each other.</i>

5
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,080
<i>Just wait and see. They won't last.</i>

6
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:21,480
<i>They'll break up for sure.</i>

7
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,760
If that girl moves in here,
she'll have to follow my rules.

8
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,240
<i>If she can't handle it, she can leave.</i>

9
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,640
We're in the same boat now.

10
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:32,040
Instead of being enemies,
wouldn't it be better to get along?

11
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:36,840
You just moved in
and already your true nature is showing.

12
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,920
My mom and your mom fought today.

13
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,680
My mom called me and told me already.

14
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:44,680
Take it easy and learn at your own pace.

15
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:50,400
At my house, we get together
every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday

16
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:51,720
at 6 p.m.

17
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:55,640
We'll have dinner and catch up on life.

18
00:02:57,320 --> 00:03:00,760
What if I miss it
or have something important to do?

19
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,840
You need to inform us one day ahead

20
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,440
because we need to prepare the food.

21
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,200
My mom will have the chef cook for us.

22
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,800
She has already sent us the menu
to choose from.

23
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,360
Tomorrow's menu will be Chinese food.

24
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:15,680
You can choose two dishes.

25
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,400
- Okay.
- What would you like to eat?

26
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,120
Here.

27
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:27,400
I'll have the deep-fried
salted egg lava bun.

28
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,240
But that's mostly dough and sugar.

29
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:32,080
Let's pick something else.

30
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,240
Chinese herbal stewed chicken
with bamboo pith, then.

31
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,320
I think chicken is too ordinary.

32
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,240
How about abalone?

33
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:45,520
Then you choose, Pun.

34
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,560
- Okay, I'll choose.
- Okay.

35
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,760
Stewed abalone with Chinese chestnuts.

36
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,760
Peking duck.

37
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,600
Scallops in XO sauce.

38
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:07,320
Steamed pomfret with soy sauce.

39
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,320
Is that okay?

40
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,040
Okay.

41
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,280
Alright, it's settled then.

42
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,040
Let's eat.

43
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:33,520
You need to hold the chopsticks
between your thumb and index finger.

44
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,680
Then,

45
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:39,200
use these three fingers
to support the chopsticks like this.

46
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,840
<i>The important thing</i>
<i>is the chopstick tips should be even.</i>

47
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,560
I'm sorry.

48
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:07,960
Take it easy, dear.

49
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,200
Okay.

50
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,760
Do you like eating leftovers?

51
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,000
Bring a new plate for Pie.

52
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,000
Pie.

53
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,720
Don't worry. We'll change the plate.

54
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,840
Okay.

55
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,880
Excuse me.

56
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,120
Thank you.

57
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,040
Let me pick it up for you.

58
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,280
Thank you, Pun.

59
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,880
Take your time eating.

60
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:11,160
Next time, if your mom is coming,

61
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,600
you need to let me know in advance.

62
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:15,400
I don't like unapproved guests showing up.

63
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,600
Yes. I'll make sure to do that.

64
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,560
About the event money

65
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:22,520
- and gifts--
- Mom.

66
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,160
I think we should just let that go.

67
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:28,840
I've already explained to Pie
how things are done in our house.

68
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,480
It's too late to know now.

69
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,720
Just wait and fix it at your next wedding.

70
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,600
She is just joking.

71
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,880
Eat more.

72
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:49,880
Pun, give her some abalone too.

73
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,000
Pie.

74
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,720
Have some scallops too.

75
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,880
Thank you.

76
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,840
Mom.

77
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,400
Pun.

78
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,480
I'm sorry.

79
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:38,440
It's my first day here,
and I've already caused trouble.

80
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,520
Pie.

81
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,640
Don't overthink it.

82
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,760
It's nothing.

83
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,480
I might not

84
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,960
be good enough, Pun.

85
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,200
I think--

86
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,480
It's nothing, Pie.

87
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:05,040
It'll pass.

88
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,840
Trust me.

89
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,400
I'm confident

90
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,040
that I didn't make the wrong choice.

91
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,600
Just go to sleep, okay?

92
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:48,880
Fon!

93
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,120
- Rok!
- Fon!

94
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:55,360
- I missed you!
- I missed you too!

95
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,960
You look prettier.

96
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,600
Just a little.

97
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,800
The weather here is nice. Sit down.

98
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:06,240
What made you invite me here?

99
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,920
I came from Thailand,
and you're meeting me at a Thai place?

100
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,040
You really don't care
that I just had Pad Kra Pao yesterday.

101
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,720
I saw that you're single,

102
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,280
just got dumped by your bad boyfriend.

103
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:21,080
I brought you here to open your world,
to see something good.

104
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,800
That way, your life will have hope.

105
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:25,920
I want to order.

106
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:27,760
Yes.

107
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:41,840
What can I get for you?

108
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:51,720
Everything looks so good. I can't decide.

109
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,480
Can I look at the menu for a second?

110
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,280
Sure.

111
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,800
I'll have the same
Thai glass noodle salad.

112
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,400
Alright.

113
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,200
- And you?
- I'm Krarok.

114
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,080
That's a cute name.

115
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,760
I mean, your name is cute.

116
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,480
I've never heard it before.

117
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,680
Would you like to order now, Ms. Krarok?

118
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:34,440
Get her the Tom Yum Goong.

119
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,280
And one plate of rice.

120
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:37,800
Got it.

121
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:38,920
Yes.

122
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,680
Please wait a moment.

123
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:42,080
Okay.

124
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:45,840
Wow, he's so handsome!

125
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:46,760
See?

126
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,200
I told you.

127
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:50,480
Nagoya's got good stuff.

128
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,600
- Forget the Pad Kra Pao you ate yesterday?
- Completely!

129
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,520
What's his name again?

130
00:10:56,600 --> 00:11:00,640
I don't know his Thai name,
but here, they call him

131
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:03,960
Mr. Shohei.

132
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:08,360
Mr. Shohei.

133
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,920
Win, talk to me for a second.

134
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,880
Do you remember when I told you
I'd be opening a branch in Osaka?

135
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:24,320
I want you to go help
as the branch manager there.

136
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,400
Be the branch manager there?

137
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,880
Yeah.

138
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,880
You can totally do it.
It's a piece of cake.

139
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,600
What you're doing now

140
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,800
is almost like being
the store manager already.

141
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,720
Only the project left, right?

142
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,280
You can do that there.

143
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:45,000
If you agree, I'll double your salary
and give you a profit share.

144
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,800
Wow.

145
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,600
You're serious?

146
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:50,960
Yeah.

147
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,560
I really want you to help out.

148
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:55,800
If you're okay with it,
you can start working right away.

149
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:09,960
MASTER OF ARTS PROGRAM IN ARCHAEOLOGY

150
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:17,440
CURRICULUM

151
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,560
Hey, boss!

152
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,440
This is my personal Facebook.

153
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,240
How can you show it like this?

154
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,880
Are you trying to shame me?

155
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,760
I'm not okay with this.

156
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,800
You think I don't know it was about me?

157
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,040
My post doesn't even mention your name.

158
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,440
If people aren't stupid,

159
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:35,640
they know I am the one giving you orders.

160
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,600
ONCE OR TWICE IS FINE. THREE TIMES?
THAT'S STUPID. TOTAL WASTE OF TIME

161
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,480
I already told you,
I wasn't talking about you.

162
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,880
Who else tells you
to revise your work besides me?

163
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,800
Or do you have another boss?

164
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,320
Oh right, I forgot.

165
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,000
You've been secretly taking side jobs.

166
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,960
I don't allow my employees
to work elsewhere,

167
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:29,160
especially not for a competitor.

168
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:30,400
But you did.

169
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,520
And you even worked on it here.

170
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:36,160
You used this company's electricity.
You used this office.

171
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,600
That alone breaks the contract.

172
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,280
If I sue you,
you'll definitely be at fault.

173
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,160
You want to settle this in court

174
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:47,040
or pack your things and leave right now?

175
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,800
Pun.

176
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,280
Please calm down first.

177
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:53,280
We can talk this through.

178
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,440
Don't waste your time

179
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,960
arguing with a stupid rich guy like me.

180
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:08,000
Go work with smarter people
somewhere else.

181
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,400
But that might be hard.

182
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,440
I've informed every company
about your behavior,

183
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,000
posting insults about your boss online.

184
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,960
No one wants an employee
who lacks emotional maturity

185
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:26,160
and commits misconduct like you.

186
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,600
Everyone, remember this.

187
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:36,280
I don't like being betrayed!

188
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:39,320
Doing something wrong
and hiding it like a secret.

189
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:42,760
Anyone who makes me feel like I'm a fool…

190
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,320
I don't keep them around!

191
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,200
Thank you.

192
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,480
Mr. Shohei.

193
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,400
Yes?

194
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:10,160
My friend is visiting.

195
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:13,520
Can she take a photo
with you as a souvenir?

196
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,040
- A photo with me?
- Yes.

197
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,440
I want to show it to my mom.

198
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:21,080
That someone said my name was cute.

199
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,000
Stand here.

200
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,480
Move closer.

201
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,440
Can you get a little closer?

202
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:33,320
Okay. One, two, three.

203
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,480
I'm so sorry.

204
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,480
Sorry.

205
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:42,360
It didn't come out right.

206
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,280
- Let's take another one.
- Let me try again.

207
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,560
One, two…

208
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,320
- Excuse me.
- What happened?

209
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,520
The oil.

210
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,080
Oil splashed onto her arm.

211
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:57,200
Rinse it with clean water
and cover it with a clean cloth.

212
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:58,880
- Quick!
- Yes.

213
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,320
Win, take her to the hospital.

214
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,400
- Excuse me.
- Take my car.

215
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,920
Excuse me.

216
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Let's go.

217
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,560
There goes our chance.

218
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,400
It's okay.

219
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:16,600
We'll come back tomorrow.

220
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,400
Tomorrow?

221
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,320
Yeah.

222
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:21,040
- Okay.
- Okay.

223
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,480
Pun.

224
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,000
I want to ask you something.

225
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:53,960
I'd like to go study
for my master's degree.

226
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,720
I don't allow it.

227
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:04,760
Why not, Pun?

228
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,800
I really want to study.

229
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:08,640
It's my dream.

230
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:12,480
When I applied for a scholarship overseas,
you never objected.

231
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:15,079
But back then, you weren't married.

232
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:17,280
Now you have a family.

233
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,640
I want you to focus on our family.

234
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,200
We're planning to have a child.

235
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:26,880
I'm not letting you study.

236
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,760
But when we were dating,

237
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:30,800
you said you'd follow me
wherever I studied.

238
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:40,040
Are you saying
my promotion period is over?

239
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,440
Alright. Fine.

240
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:53,400
Go ahead and study.

241
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,680
Really?

242
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,680
But…

243
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,760
Family comes first.

244
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:05,640
If you neglect it,
I won't be okay with that.

245
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,040
Understand?

246
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,280
I understand.

247
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:11,840
Family will always come first, Pun.

248
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:16,800
Thank you.

249
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:20,040
<i>I'm not okay with that.</i>

250
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:21,600
You're married,
and your husband gave you a job.

251
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,480
Why quit to go study?

252
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,440
Mom, please let me study.

253
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:28,760
I just want some time for myself.

254
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,560
Mom, these days,

255
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:34,280
I'm with Pun almost 24 hours a day
at home and at work.

256
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:35,240
Pie.

257
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:37,480
You just got married a few days ago.

258
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:39,160
Why are you thinking like this?

259
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,320
This is supposed
to be the honeymoon phase.

260
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,200
You shouldn't be complaining like this.

261
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:45,720
Besides, when you're married,

262
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,360
you should want to be close to each other.

263
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,240
Why create distance?

264
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:53,440
I understand, Mom. I really do.

265
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:56,080
But I just want to do
something I like, that's all.

266
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:02,160
If you want something
to love and care about,

267
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,800
then hurry up and have a baby.

268
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,920
Once you have a child, you won't have time

269
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,040
to overthink or want to do other things.

270
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,800
And I promise, once you have a baby,

271
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:13,080
you'll want to stay even closer.

272
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:15,280
Your love will definitely last.

273
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:20,800
Mom.

274
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:22,720
You had a child with Dad. Did it last?

275
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,920
Pie, are you talking back to me?

276
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,080
No, I'm not.

277
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:32,160
I'm just saying, if your way didn't work,

278
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,720
then please let me study.

279
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:35,800
I've thought about it, Mom.

280
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,440
If I get to do something for myself,

281
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:40,080
my relationship with Pun
will last even longer.

282
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,880
Please, Mom. Let me go study.

283
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,800
I'm begging you. Please.

284
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:45,800
I'm begging you.

285
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,680
I really want to study.

286
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,160
Pun already agreed to let me go.
Please, Mom.

287
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,440
I'm begging you, Mom.

288
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,760
- Please!
- Fine!

289
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,560
If you want to study, then go!

290
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,040
Really, Mom?

291
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:58,320
But

292
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:02,160
when you have a baby, you have to quit.

293
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:03,960
Okay.

294
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,200
Love you, Mom.

295
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:16,240
Mr. Shohei moved to the Osaka branch?

296
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:18,280
Yes, he just left this morning.

297
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:19,800
But if you want to see him,

298
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:21,680
you can try the new branch in Osaka.

299
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:24,560
I guarantee the food
tastes exactly the same as here.

300
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:30,200
- Fon!
- Hey, it's okay.

301
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:32,080
Next time you visit,

302
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:37,160
I promise I'll take you to Osaka myself.

303
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:38,240
Hey.

304
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:40,720
I'm not in the mood for love anymore.

305
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:43,680
I think I'm cursed to stay single,
and I have to accept it.

306
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:44,640
I'm done chasing love.

307
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,320
I'm not looking for it anymore.

308
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,320
I'm done!

309
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,560
Rok.

310
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,040
You've been watching too much anime.

311
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,280
Hey!

312
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,200
Excuse me.

313
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:59,600
May I sit in this seat?

314
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,280
This is your boyfriend?

315
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,360
Yes!

316
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:28,040
Toshi and I
met at a Thai restaurant in Nagoya.

317
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,440
It was a coincidence.

318
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:31,480
He was about to travel to Thailand anyway,

319
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:33,960
so I invited him to come with me.

320
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:38,080
He's half Thai, half Japanese.

321
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:40,240
His mom taught him Thai
since he was little.

322
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:41,320
And guess what?

323
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,120
His mom's old house is near my house.

324
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:45,920
Isn't that destiny?

325
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,720
Sure!

326
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:51,200
Five days in Japan
and you came back with a boyfriend.

327
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:53,840
If that's not destiny,
I don't know what is.

328
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,760
Come on.

329
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,800
Let's celebrate
the new things in our lives.

330
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:02,200
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

331
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,120
‪-It's tasty.
‪-Yeah.

332
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,040
Please, go ahead.

333
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,160
- Is it good?
- Thank you.

334
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:30,080
FACULTY OF ARCHAEOLOGY

335
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:32,520
ARCHAEOLOGY ALUMNI ASSOCIATION

336
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,920
Hello, Professor.

337
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,720
How are you?

338
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:39,280
Mrs. Executive.

339
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:41,600
I hate that.

340
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:44,240
So, are you sure about this?

341
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:46,040
A master's program is tough.

342
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:49,000
And get ready for the headache
called a thesis.

343
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,840
I'm ready. Bring it on. I love this stuff.

344
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,960
Still as hardcore as ever.

345
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:55,160
Here are the application details.

346
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,120
Thank you.

347
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:59,600
You could've checked this online.
No need to come here.

348
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:03,280
Actually, I came because I wanted
to ask you something.

349
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,320
Professor.

350
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:09,320
While I'm studying,
could I work as a teaching assistant too?

351
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,960
You're good at giving yourself extra work.

352
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:15,280
Just a warning.
Studying alone is already heavy.

353
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:18,640
If you become a TA,
you won't have time to have fun.

354
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:21,040
That's okay. I can handle it.

355
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:23,080
Please let me do it.

356
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,760
I can come to the university every day.

357
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:27,840
Morning to evening, every day.
Even weekends.

358
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,880
Don't you plan on going home at all?

359
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:38,880
Seriously?

360
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:41,760
Why?

361
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:44,560
Don't you want to go home?

362
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:52,560
Professor.

363
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:54,320
Please don't tell Pun.

364
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,080
Did you two fight?

365
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,480
No, we didn't.

366
00:23:57,560 --> 00:24:00,000
Pun takes very good care of me.

367
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,840
I get it now.

368
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:07,000
Pun does like taking care of people.

369
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:10,440
But he does it because he wants
everything to go his way.

370
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:14,720
Sometimes,
he forgets what you actually want, right?

371
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:21,200
- Yes.
- Married life

372
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,480
isn't always what we imagine, Pie.

373
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:28,720
Sometimes love and happiness
go in opposite directions.

374
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:31,080
But if we choose to love someone,

375
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,560
we have to be patient

376
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:34,440
and try to adjust.

377
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,920
You can do it. I believe in you.

378
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:41,360
Now go get ready.

379
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:44,560
Being a TA is brutal.

380
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:47,880
As long as I get to help teach,
I can handle anything.

381
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,640
Excellent. I'll be watching.

382
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:20,640
TWO YEARS LATER

383
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:40,280
KLICK AS
PREGNANCY TEST

384
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:47,360
How is it?

385
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:52,520
KLICK AS
PREGNANCY TEST

386
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:57,440
Pie.

387
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:01,440
It's been over two years now.

388
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,760
Have you been taking
good care of yourself?

389
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,520
I've done everything you told me to.

390
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:09,760
Are you sure?

391
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:11,200
Yes.

392
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:13,160
I eat healthy.

393
00:29:13,240 --> 00:29:14,880
No coffee, no alcohol.

394
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:16,800
I sleep eight hours every night.

395
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:19,000
When is your next ovulation?

396
00:29:19,520 --> 00:29:22,400
Bring me your schedule so we can plan it.

397
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:25,080
I'll try a new position
and see if it works.

398
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:28,520
I think we're already way behind schedule.

399
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:32,640
Hey.

400
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:35,840
You need to take better care
of yourself these days.

401
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:39,840
Next time, I really
want us to have a baby.

402
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:42,600
Okay?

403
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:48,080
Okay.

404
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,320
<i>Have you ever noticed?</i>

405
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:58,720
<i>Some people are right next to each other,</i>

406
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:01,040
<i>yet it feels like they're miles apart.</i>

407
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:03,080
<i>But with some people who are far away…</i>

408
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,000
I SAY IT LIKE THIS

409
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:06,320
<i>…it feels like they're with you</i>
<i>all the time.</i>

410
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:10,440
<i>When my boyfriend was far away,</i>
<i>it really felt far.</i>

411
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:13,840
<i>So far that he couldn't take it anymore</i>
<i>and broke up with me.</i>

412
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:16,840
<i>Do you think he was using distance</i>
<i>as an excuse?</i>

413
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:19,160
Definitely.

414
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:21,120
It has to be an excuse.

415
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,400
Rok!

416
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:32,800
Rok.

417
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,000
What's wrong? Why are you crying?

418
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:38,360
- What happened?
- Pie.

419
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:39,280
What?

420
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:43,800
Toshi broke up with me yesterday.

421
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:44,920
Huh?

422
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:48,640
He said long-distance relationships
don't work.

423
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:50,720
Don't cry.

424
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:09,080
I feel a bit better.
At least good food helps.

425
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:11,600
So good.

426
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:14,480
Thanks for treating me to cheer me up.

427
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,080
It's fine.

428
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:18,040
I get to eat to distract myself too.

429
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:22,600
Did it work yet?

430
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,400
Not yet.

431
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,480
It's okay.

432
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:30,680
Try again next ovulation, okay?

433
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,760
<i>Hey, I've graduated!</i>

434
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,040
<i>I'm about to go back to Thailand.</i>

435
00:31:42,120 --> 00:31:43,160
<i>Let's meet when I'm back.</i>

436
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,000
Hey.

437
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:46,720
Mink graduated.

438
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,160
She's coming back to Thailand.

439
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:50,240
- Really?
- She just sent this.

440
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:53,000
Lucky her, right?

441
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:56,280
When we graduated, we should've gone too.

442
00:31:56,800 --> 00:31:57,760
Yeah.

443
00:31:58,280 --> 00:32:00,560
I should've chosen
to study abroad back then.

444
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:02,360
I shouldn't have given in.

445
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,320
Too late now, future mom.

446
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,480
Just send your kid to study instead.

447
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,920
Oh, it's already afternoon.

448
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:14,320
Hey, can you pay first?
I'll transfer the money to you.

449
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,480
I have to go. I have a class.

450
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:16,720
- Hey!
- What?

451
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,360
Let the students wait a bit.

452
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:20,480
No, I can't be late.

453
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:22,200
My personal life right now

454
00:32:22,280 --> 00:32:24,200
has to follow Pun
and his family's schedule.

455
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:28,280
Teaching is the only thing
that makes me happy right now.

456
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:30,440
So I'm not going to be late.

457
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:31,960
I'm off. See you.

458
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:33,840
- Bye.
- Bye.

459
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:37,960
In this course,

460
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:41,680
students will discuss
anthropological concepts and theories

461
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:45,640
related to community-based
cultural heritage management.

462
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:13,800
<i>If you remember,</i>
<i>about five or six years ago,</i>

463
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:18,800
<i>a comet called Comet Wirtanen</i>
<i>passed by Thailand.</i>

464
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:23,480
<i>It was clearly visible</i>
<i>and created quite a lot of excitement.</i>

465
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:26,040
<i>So, who here remembers seeing it?</i>

466
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:28,800
<i>Did anyone miss it?</i>

467
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:55,360
<i>But if you did miss it, don't worry.</i>

468
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:57,480
<i>Because this May,</i>

469
00:33:57,560 --> 00:34:01,480
<i>Comet Wirtanen</i>
<i>will be passing by Thailand again.</i>

470
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:04,880
<i>And this time, you definitely</i>
<i>don't want to miss it.</i>

471
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:39,800
MOM

472
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,840
Yes, Mom.

473
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:44,320
I'm already waiting.

474
00:34:48,199 --> 00:34:50,000
Okay, I'll wait for you at the exit.

475
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:51,400
Alright.

476
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:04,640
- I'm here, Pie!
- Mom!

477
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:08,000
Come here. Hello, Mom.

478
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:13,720
I missed you so much.

479
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:16,240
- How was your trip, Mom?
- Amazing!

480
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:20,240
I had so much fun shopping.
I bought tons of things for you.

481
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:21,640
Wow, Mom.

482
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:23,960
Should we go look at them at home?

483
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:25,000
- I have another appointment.
- Really?

484
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:28,360
- Yes.
- I want to show them to you right now.

485
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:46,280
Here's your share
and the bonus for helping out.

486
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:48,040
It's my way of thanking you

487
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:50,280
for helping until the Osaka branch
got on its feet.

488
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:51,680
Thanks a lot.

489
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:57,480
I hope only good things
come your way back in Thailand.

490
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,840
Thank you so much.

491
00:36:13,480 --> 00:36:15,720
<i>Why is there so much traffic?</i>

492
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:21,040
Does that family still keep the tradition
of having to eat together?

493
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:23,200
If they didn't, why would I be rushing?

494
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:25,360
If I'm late, someone's
going to be unhappy again.

495
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,760
Serve the rice. We're not waiting anymore.

496
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:49,600
I'm sorry I'm late.

497
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:51,520
I'm sorry.

498
00:36:53,720 --> 00:36:55,000
If you can't even be on time,

499
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:57,040
how are you going
to take care of a family?

500
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,280
I'm sorry.

501
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:00,360
Pie.

502
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,840
Why didn't you call me first?

503
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,680
I'm sorry, Pun.

504
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:05,120
I was rushing while driving.

505
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,920
You don't like me calling
while driving, so I didn't call.

506
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:10,440
That's enough apologizing.
You're here now.

507
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:11,440
Let's eat.

508
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:13,360
Come sit.

509
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:17,520
I'm sorry.

510
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:25,800
My mom bought some gifts for you both.

511
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:26,880
Tian.

512
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:32,400
The big bag is for Dad,
and the small one is for Mom.

513
00:37:35,240 --> 00:37:37,360
This is for you, sir.

514
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:39,120
And this is for you, ma'am.

515
00:37:47,080 --> 00:37:48,400
This is beautiful.

516
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:50,120
She has great taste.

517
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,000
Please thank your mother for me.

518
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:53,560
Of course.

519
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:57,560
Tian.

520
00:37:58,880 --> 00:37:59,600
Take it away.

521
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:03,520
You can keep it or sell it. I don't care.

522
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:05,800
After all, these things

523
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:08,640
were bought with my family's money anyway.

524
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,080
Are you going to argue with that?

525
00:38:27,720 --> 00:38:28,880
Let's eat.

526
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:32,680
- Come on. Let's eat.
- Yes.

527
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:33,840
Alright.

528
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:34,920
Let's eat.

529
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:56,400
Your wedding anniversary
is coming up soon.

530
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:59,960
But we've held it at hotels
for many years already.

531
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:02,160
This year, let's have it at home.

532
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:04,080
Pie and I will host it ourselves.

533
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,640
I don't trust anyone else.

534
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:16,240
I'm only comfortable
letting you handle it alone.

535
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,160
Pie.

536
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:58,960
Don't think too much

537
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,760
about what my mom said.

538
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:07,160
You can still help me organize the event.

539
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:12,960
It's okay, Pun.

540
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:17,200
I don't want any problems with your mom.

541
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,840
Let's just do what she's comfortable with.

542
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:24,600
Alright then.

543
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:27,920
But…

544
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:31,040
if you change your mind and want to help,

545
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,920
just tell me.

546
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:37,120
Okay.

547
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,240
There you go.

548
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,960
That's the Pie I love.

549
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,280
No drama.

550
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:47,880
Easygoing.

551
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:49,000
Fine with anything.

552
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,440
Being with you
makes me feel so comfortable.

553
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:05,760
I think…

554
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:11,080
We haven't gone to bed together
for several nights now.

555
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:14,400
Let's go to bed early together tonight.

556
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,120
Pun.

557
00:42:08,720 --> 00:42:10,160
I still…

558
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:12,040
have some work to finish.

559
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:15,320
You should go to bed first.

560
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:17,920
Don't wait for me.

561
00:43:04,360 --> 00:43:05,640
Aunt Saen!

562
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:11,600
Your new husband?

563
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:13,520
He asked me for directions.

564
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:23,680
- Why did he bow to me?
- Bye.

565
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:24,600
That was smooth.

566
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:26,640
Come on. Get in the car.

567
00:43:26,720 --> 00:43:28,320
I've prepared your room. Hurry up.

568
00:43:30,120 --> 00:43:31,720
Did you get a new haircut?

569
00:43:34,440 --> 00:43:35,840
You look gorgeous.

570
00:43:52,640 --> 00:43:53,640
Come in.

571
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,000
These are your things.

572
00:43:58,080 --> 00:43:59,680
I kept everything for you.

573
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:03,160
Thank you.

574
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:07,200
Hey, you disappeared for so long.

575
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:08,760
Do you have a girlfriend yet?

576
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:09,960
No.

577
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:13,440
There's only one person
I keep thinking about.

578
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:18,960
You miss her, but does she know?

579
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:29,000
I don't use social media.
I haven't contacted anyone.

580
00:44:29,520 --> 00:44:30,800
I was afraid I'd get distracted.

581
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:33,360
Every day, it's just work and studying.

582
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:35,680
Look at you.

583
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:38,040
Becoming so responsible.

584
00:44:38,120 --> 00:44:39,680
All for a girl, right?

585
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:44,240
What if she's married and has a child?

586
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:46,800
If she's happy,

587
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:49,200
I'm okay with that.

588
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:53,800
And what if she's not happy?

589
00:45:08,520 --> 00:45:10,360
Oh my!

590
00:45:10,440 --> 00:45:11,560
Oh my goodness!

591
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:13,560
Welcome home!

592
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:14,920
I missed you so much.

593
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:16,240
I missed you too.

594
00:45:19,240 --> 00:45:21,320
And I really missed Thai food.

595
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:22,720
Oh my goodness.

596
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:25,160
Aren't there lots of Thai restaurants
in England?

597
00:45:25,240 --> 00:45:27,520
But it's not the same
as the food you make.

598
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:28,800
Such a sweet talker.

599
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,800
I've already prepared something for you.

600
00:45:30,880 --> 00:45:32,080
Oh!

601
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:34,440
Someone wants to see you too.

602
00:45:34,520 --> 00:45:35,960
Who?

603
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:40,480
- Hello, Auntie.
- Mungmink!

604
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:42,040
I've missed you so much, dear.

605
00:45:42,560 --> 00:45:44,640
I've missed you too, Auntie.

606
00:45:44,720 --> 00:45:45,600
Look at you.

607
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:47,920
You just get prettier and prettier.

608
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:49,440
What a shame.

609
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:51,520
My son just didn't have the sense
to choose you.

610
00:45:51,600 --> 00:45:53,960
Sit down. Shall we eat first?

611
00:45:57,240 --> 00:46:00,040
Eating with you
really puts my mind at ease.

612
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:02,720
Unlike when I eat with that one.

613
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:04,240
Who?

614
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:05,880
Pun's wife, of course.

615
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:08,040
So clumsy and awkward.

616
00:46:08,120 --> 00:46:10,040
Nothing she does is right.

617
00:46:10,120 --> 00:46:11,560
Nothing about her looks proper.

618
00:46:12,480 --> 00:46:14,880
She clearly wasn't raised well.

619
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:16,480
Unlike you.

620
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:19,160
Oh, come on.

621
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:22,360
With all that gossip,
she must be sneezing nonstop.

622
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:24,920
So what? It's all true anyway.

623
00:46:25,880 --> 00:46:27,640
Let's eat!

624
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:29,600
- Let me serve you, Auntie.
- Thank you, dear.

625
00:46:30,400 --> 00:46:34,520
Honestly, you should've
been part of our family.

626
00:46:35,040 --> 00:46:36,800
Such a shame.

627
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:38,880
I don't know how Pun
ended up marrying that girl.

628
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:41,880
Don't stress yourself out.

629
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:43,600
You won't look good at the party tomorrow.

630
00:46:43,680 --> 00:46:45,160
Oh right, I forgot.

631
00:46:45,680 --> 00:46:46,800
No stress.

632
00:46:46,880 --> 00:46:48,040
Exactly.

633
00:46:48,120 --> 00:46:50,040
But you're not coming.

634
00:46:50,120 --> 00:46:52,400
I'm so sorry. I really can't go.

635
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:55,240
I have to go on a cultural tour in Egypt.

636
00:46:55,840 --> 00:46:56,800
Don't say anything.

637
00:46:56,880 --> 00:46:58,360
What party?

638
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:15,640
Pie.

639
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:17,440
Pie.

640
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:20,600
Pie!

641
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:22,560
Oh my goodness. Wake up!

642
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:24,920
Come on. Get up. Wake up!

643
00:47:28,320 --> 00:47:29,280
Oh, good.

644
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:31,440
I thought the party had already started.

645
00:47:32,520 --> 00:47:33,320
Pie!

646
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:35,800
You can't wake up
right when the event starts.

647
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:37,520
Get up right now.

648
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:40,200
Why aren't you downstairs helping out?

649
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:43,040
Today is your in-laws'
wedding anniversary.

650
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:45,000
Get up and go help.

651
00:47:45,080 --> 00:47:46,040
Mom.

652
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:48,440
Nothing I do ever pleases Pun's mom.

653
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:50,360
If I help, she'll just get more annoyed.

654
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:53,560
When it's time for me to appear,
someone will come get me.

655
00:47:53,640 --> 00:47:55,440
No, Pie!

656
00:47:55,520 --> 00:47:58,080
Get up right now.

657
00:47:58,160 --> 00:48:00,600
Go help them.

658
00:48:00,680 --> 00:48:02,520
Be a good daughter-in-law,

659
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:04,680
or they'll say
I didn't raise you properly.

660
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:06,200
Come on. Hurry.

661
00:48:07,560 --> 00:48:10,560
By the way, where's the gift?

662
00:48:10,640 --> 00:48:12,000
There isn't one.

663
00:48:12,080 --> 00:48:13,920
What?

664
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:16,960
That won't do. That would look terrible.

665
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:19,840
Mom, they said
we didn't need to bring anything.

666
00:48:19,920 --> 00:48:22,640
That's just polite talk.

667
00:48:22,720 --> 00:48:24,280
If you show up with nothing,

668
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:26,960
they'll think you have no manners.

669
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:31,080
Good thing I was careful.

670
00:48:34,160 --> 00:48:37,800
Here, Korean ginseng.

671
00:48:38,480 --> 00:48:41,320
Give it to your in-laws.

672
00:48:41,400 --> 00:48:43,080
It costs tens of thousands.

673
00:48:43,160 --> 00:48:44,680
Mom, isn't that too expensive?

674
00:48:45,440 --> 00:48:48,720
If we give something cheap,
they'll think we're poor.

675
00:48:49,440 --> 00:48:51,920
Today, they'll probably think
you're very rich.

676
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:52,840
Look at you.

677
00:48:54,240 --> 00:48:57,280
Head-to-toe designer
and diamonds everywhere.

678
00:48:58,160 --> 00:49:00,960
Mom, how much did you rent all that for?

679
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:03,200
However much I rented it for
is my business.

680
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:06,160
Pie, the team is ready.

681
00:49:07,720 --> 00:49:09,360
- Hello, Mom.
- Hello.

682
00:49:09,440 --> 00:49:11,680
I brought a team
to do Pie's hair and makeup.

683
00:49:12,840 --> 00:49:14,760
Oh my.

684
00:49:14,840 --> 00:49:17,880
My daughter must have done
a lot of good deeds

685
00:49:17,960 --> 00:49:21,600
to get such a wonderful husband.

686
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:23,760
You also got a wonderful son-in-law.

687
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:26,720
Because I prepared
an outfit for you as well.

688
00:49:28,720 --> 00:49:30,440
- Oh…
- Well…

689
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:33,960
I want everyone at the party
to wear auspicious colors.

690
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:36,240
So I took the liberty
of preparing one for you too.

691
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:39,640
You can try it on now.
I already told the team.

692
00:49:40,680 --> 00:49:41,680
Alright.

693
00:49:42,280 --> 00:49:44,000
And besides the outfits,

694
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:48,200
I've also prepared
a gift for my parents for you.

695
00:49:51,240 --> 00:49:55,440
One box from Pie and me,
and one box from you.

696
00:49:56,560 --> 00:50:00,160
That's okay. I already prepared a gift.

697
00:50:00,240 --> 00:50:01,160
Here, Pun.

698
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:04,320
Korean ginseng.

699
00:50:04,400 --> 00:50:06,440
Mom, actually,

700
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:09,600
a friend of my mom's just started
importing Korean ginseng.

701
00:50:09,680 --> 00:50:11,120
Our house is full of it.

702
00:50:11,200 --> 00:50:12,440
We couldn't finish it in a year.

703
00:50:13,040 --> 00:50:13,960
This one's better.

704
00:50:14,040 --> 00:50:15,160
It's more appropriate.

705
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:16,800
Trust me, Mom.

706
00:50:20,840 --> 00:50:21,800
Alright.

707
00:50:22,320 --> 00:50:23,840
If you say so.

708
00:50:25,320 --> 00:50:26,160
Yes.

709
00:50:34,920 --> 00:50:38,600
- Everything's done properly, Mom.
- Hello, Nhun.

710
00:50:38,680 --> 00:50:39,520
Hello.

711
00:50:39,600 --> 00:50:41,080
Happy anniversary.

712
00:50:41,160 --> 00:50:44,240
I wish you both a lifetime of love.

713
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:46,760
This is just a small gift.

714
00:50:46,840 --> 00:50:48,680
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

715
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:50,000
Thank you.

716
00:50:50,080 --> 00:50:52,200
You really didn't have to. We're family.

717
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:53,960
Oh no.

718
00:50:54,040 --> 00:50:57,040
I couldn't come empty-handed
on such an important day.

719
00:51:00,840 --> 00:51:04,080
Mom, this one is from Pie and me.

720
00:51:04,680 --> 00:51:05,880
Thank you, dear.

721
00:51:07,800 --> 00:51:08,760
The dress looks nice.

722
00:51:09,640 --> 00:51:11,000
- Thank you.
- Pun chose well.

723
00:51:12,040 --> 00:51:13,880
But you're too thin.

724
00:51:14,640 --> 00:51:16,200
You don't fill out the dress.

725
00:51:19,440 --> 00:51:20,480
Oh, come on.

726
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:26,120
My parents and I didn't bring a gift,

727
00:51:26,200 --> 00:51:28,240
but my mom asked me to say she misses you.

728
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:31,520
She'll bring her 48-hour braised eggs
for you and Uncle Sil.

729
00:51:32,120 --> 00:51:32,960
- Alright.
- Thank you.

730
00:51:33,040 --> 00:51:35,240
That alone makes me very happy.

731
00:51:35,320 --> 00:51:36,320
Yes.

732
00:51:40,320 --> 00:51:41,240
Mom.

733
00:51:41,320 --> 00:51:42,880
Dad, let's head inside first.

734
00:51:42,960 --> 00:51:44,360
- The guests are waiting.
- Alright.

735
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:48,520
- Pie, go help greet the guests. Hurry.
- Okay.

736
00:51:49,400 --> 00:51:50,240
No need.

737
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:54,200
The people here are all family.

738
00:51:54,280 --> 00:51:57,120
I'll greet my guests myself.

739
00:52:04,080 --> 00:52:06,360
Pie, go inside first.

740
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:09,880
Hey, come sit with me.

741
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:12,520
I have so much to tell you.

742
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:13,440
Come on. Let's go.

743
00:52:13,520 --> 00:52:14,800
Alright.

744
00:52:14,880 --> 00:52:15,880
Let's go, Pie.

745
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:26,920
Mom, can't you go a little easier on Pie?

746
00:52:28,560 --> 00:52:30,160
I have nothing against your wife.

747
00:52:30,240 --> 00:52:31,600
You're the one behind it all.

748
00:52:32,120 --> 00:52:33,680
Don't think I can't tell

749
00:52:33,760 --> 00:52:36,080
those two gift boxes
were entirely your doing.

750
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:38,880
Can't you just pretend not to notice?

751
00:52:38,960 --> 00:52:40,160
No.

752
00:52:43,840 --> 00:52:46,960
Happy anniversary!

753
00:52:47,040 --> 00:52:47,880
Now.

754
00:52:55,080 --> 00:52:56,240
Look at the cake.

755
00:52:58,640 --> 00:53:00,000
Alright.

756
00:53:08,840 --> 00:53:12,200
Nhun, did you make a wish
when you cut the cake?

757
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:15,640
What I want most right now
is a grandchild.

758
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:20,760
You'll have one very soon.

759
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:24,320
You've been saying that since the wedding.

760
00:53:24,400 --> 00:53:26,160
It's been two years already.

761
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:28,160
We still haven't held a grandchild.

762
00:53:28,240 --> 00:53:30,000
This year for sure, Dad.

763
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:33,160
Pie will quit her job
to prepare for having a baby.

764
00:53:33,240 --> 00:53:34,520
Quit my job?

765
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,360
Pun?

766
00:53:42,160 --> 00:53:43,920
Shouldn't you two talk about that first?

767
00:53:46,440 --> 00:53:48,200
I just haven't told Pie yet, Mom.

768
00:53:48,280 --> 00:53:50,320
She'll cooperate anyway.

769
00:53:55,480 --> 00:53:57,120
No problem, right?

770
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:09,120
No problem!

771
00:54:09,200 --> 00:54:10,760
No problem at all.

772
00:54:10,840 --> 00:54:14,480
Pie is completely ready,
mentally and physically.

773
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:16,800
You'll have a grandchild very soon.

774
00:54:25,760 --> 00:54:26,960
Pun.

775
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:28,720
You're joking, right?

776
00:54:29,360 --> 00:54:30,560
I'm serious.

777
00:54:31,960 --> 00:54:34,440
And I'm going to do exactly what I said.

778
00:54:34,520 --> 00:54:35,680
I mean it.

779
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:39,080
But we agreed
that I would get pregnant first,

780
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:40,920
and then I'd quit my job.

781
00:54:43,120 --> 00:54:44,440
I thought about it.

782
00:54:45,280 --> 00:54:46,720
What if you get pregnant
during the semester?

783
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:48,040
Who would teach your classes?

784
00:54:48,640 --> 00:54:50,880
I can keep teaching
until the semester ends.

785
00:54:50,960 --> 00:54:53,840
Other people work
until seven or eight months.

786
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:56,200
But your body isn't like other people's.

787
00:54:56,280 --> 00:54:58,080
Having a baby hasn't been easy for us.

788
00:54:58,160 --> 00:55:00,520
It's been over two years,
and there's nothing yet.

789
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:04,880
If you get pregnant and keep working,

790
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:07,360
what if there are complications?

791
00:55:07,440 --> 00:55:09,080
I'm not taking that risk.

792
00:55:11,040 --> 00:55:14,000
I already talked to the dean. He agreed.

793
00:55:14,640 --> 00:55:15,960
You talked to the dean?

794
00:55:16,040 --> 00:55:16,880
Yes.

795
00:55:16,960 --> 00:55:19,200
You didn't think to tell me first?

796
00:55:22,760 --> 00:55:24,720
I don't see why I needed to.

797
00:55:25,840 --> 00:55:27,600
I'm sure what I choose

798
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:30,880
is what's best for you.

799
00:55:33,040 --> 00:55:34,840
Even if I had told you beforehand,

800
00:55:35,360 --> 00:55:36,960
you wouldn't have agreed anyway.

801
00:55:37,880 --> 00:55:39,040
Am I right?

802
00:55:47,560 --> 00:55:49,480
Pie, come on.

803
00:55:50,040 --> 00:55:51,120
Listen to me.

804
00:55:52,320 --> 00:55:56,160
You're at the best
and safest age to have a baby right now.

805
00:55:57,600 --> 00:56:00,040
I made all these decisions

806
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:03,760
for our family.

807
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:06,720
You understand me, right?

808
00:56:38,920 --> 00:56:41,240
Pun, my stomach hurts.

809
00:57:33,040 --> 00:57:35,600
<i>I want to turn great grandma's house</i>
<i>into a cafe.</i>

810
00:57:35,680 --> 00:57:39,240
But you have to help me
build the museum too.

811
00:57:39,320 --> 00:57:40,720
What museum?

812
00:57:40,800 --> 00:57:42,280
<i>I want you to do this job.</i>

813
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:44,960
Because I'm sure Uncle Dech will like you.

814
00:57:45,040 --> 00:57:47,280
And if you do it, it'll make my mom--

815
00:57:47,360 --> 00:57:48,680
Like me too?

816
00:57:49,720 --> 00:57:51,280
Do you still have a problem with Pie?

817
00:57:52,040 --> 00:57:54,080
Don't tell me you still like Pun.

818
00:57:55,400 --> 00:57:56,120
‪Koh!

819
00:57:59,840 --> 00:58:01,320
You've really grown up.

820
00:58:01,400 --> 00:58:04,560
That habit of sneaking around
behind your husband's back,

821
00:58:04,640 --> 00:58:05,920
you should stop it.

822
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:07,360
Secrets never stay hidden.

823
00:58:12,720 --> 00:58:14,440
- Calm down!
- Get out!

824
00:58:14,520 --> 00:58:15,800
That's enough. Stop!

825
00:58:15,880 --> 00:58:17,120
<i>He's my friend.</i>

826
00:58:17,200 --> 00:58:19,320
<i>And Pie is my wife.</i>

827
00:58:48,200 --> 00:58:50,840
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
